amend: add host-dependent EXPECTED-value pitfall (machine-specific absolute path baked into a golden) + full-parametrized-run lesson (verified-ci)

- **Changed by**: ProjectHephaestus PR #1621 — machine-path test portability
- **Verification**: verified-ci
- **What changed**:
  - When to Use: new trigger (14) — agent/dev hardcodes a machine-specific absolute path (or other host/env-derived value) into an EXPECTED/golden so it passes on the authoring host but fails on CI; derive from the production constant the code interpolates and run the FULL parametrized test
  - Quick Reference: section 12 (host-dependent EXPECTED value — green local / red CI)
  - Detailed Steps: Step 12 (machine-specific absolute path baked into a golden; fix = `f"``{DEFAULT_PROJECTS_DIR}``"` derived from the same constant the parser interpolates; run FULL parametrized test, not a subset)
