- **Why**: an agent baked its OWN host's absolute path into `EXPECTED_SPECS` for the `loop_runner` `--projects-dir` help text. The help string interpolates `DEFAULT_PROJECTS_DIR` (per-host: `~/Projects`, or `/mnt/weka/home/micah.villmow/Projects` on the authoring machine), so the test was green on that machine and RED on every CI runner. Fix imports the production constant and builds the expected value via f-string from the same source the parser uses. Also: a narrowed local subset run masked the failing parametrization — the FULL matrix ran on CI and failed.

